ustry video game industry revenue us million  operating income us− million  net income us− million  total assets us billion  total equity us billion  employees  dec  website wwwzyngacom registration yes users  million monthly active users  million daily active users q zynga ˈzɪŋɡə is an american video game developer running social video game services founded in july  and headquartered in san francisco california united states the company develops social games that work standalone on mobile phone platforms such as apple ios android windows phone and on the internet through its website zyngacom and social networking websites such as facebook google and tencent qq zynga states its mission as connecting the world through games the company was named in honor of zinga ceo mark pincuss deceased american bulldog zynga launched its bestknown game farmville on facebook in june  reaching  million daily active users dau within six weeks as of early january  zynga games had over  million monthly active users mau and three of the top five facebook games in terms of mau according to appdata were zynga titles farmville  texas holdem poker now known as zynga poker and chefville according to the bbc around  percent of zyngas revenue comes from facebook users but its formal partnership with facebook ended on march   zynga began trading on nasdaq december   under the ticker znga originally priced at  znga shares reached a price of  in march  but fell steadily after that point hitting  in  some analysts and journalists have questioned the longterm prospects of zynga’s business model especially after zynga’s q  earnings report failed to meet analyst projections for revenue and earnings zynga has been taking steps to cut expenses and expand its business into areas such as licensed board games online gambling its own gaming platform zyngacom and mobile game apps contents  history  acquisitions  revenue  business model  hasbro partnership  realmoney gaming  customer acquisition  platinum pu